{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"title","type":"text","text":"<div style='text-align:center'>\n\n<span style='font-size:44px'><b>Development Roadmap</b></span>\n\n<span style='font-size:22px'>The build order, left to right — not a feature tree ([[Meridian Overview.canvas|see that]]) but a timeline of <b>stages</b>, each one shipped before the next starts. <b>🟢 means the mechanic exists and runs, NOT that it's as deep/realistic as the final vision</b> — depth is its own ongoing axis, see stage 4.5. 🟡 = next up/in progress · ⚪ = planned · 🟣 = release milestone.</span>\n\n</div>","x":-40,"y":-560,"width":4360,"height":320},
		{"id":"s1","type":"text","text":"<div style='text-align:center'>\n\n<span style='font-size:34px'><b>1 · Foundation</b></span>\n\n<span style='font-size:18px'>Geo data pipeline (Natural Earth → Web Mercator), map rendering (country meshes, borders, provinces, cities, roads/rail), pan/zoom camera, core economy tick.</span>\n\n<span style='font-size:16px'><i>🟢 Core built</i> — [[Geo Pipeline|→]] [[Map Rendering|→]] [[Camera and Input|→]]</span>\n\n</div>","x":0,"y":0,"width":480,"height":320,"color":"#2f9e44"},
		{"id":"s2","type":"text","text":"<div style='text-align:center'>\n\n<span style='font-size:34px'><b>2 · World Systems</b></span>\n\n<span style='font-size:18px'>Budget spending levers, decision events, diplomacy (relations/aid/trade/denounce), war & military with autonomous World AI, save/load.</span>\n\n<span style='font-size:16px'><i>🟢 Core built</i> — [[Diplomacy System|→]] [[War System|→]] [[Save Load|→]]</span>\n\n</div>","x":540,"y":0,"width":480,"height":320,"color":"#2f9e44"},
		{"id":"s3","type":"text","text":"<div style='text-align:center'>\n\n<span style='font-size:34px'><b>3 · Depth & UI Pass</b></span>\n\n<span style='font-size:18px'>Population dynamics + credit rating + debt interest, full UI overhaul (cards, progress bars, area-chart sparklines, real dates, severity toasts), camera frame clamp, relation-based Political fill / Satellite border coloring, this vault.</span>\n\n<span style='font-size:16px'><i>🟢 Core built</i> — [[Economy System|→]] [[UI System|→]] [[Map Modes and Coloring|→]]</span>\n\n</div>","x":1080,"y":0,"width":480,"height":320,"color":"#2f9e44"},
		{"id":"s4","type":"text","text":"<div style='text-align:center'>\n\n<span style='font-size:34px'><b>4 · Remaining Features</b></span>\n\n<span style='font-size:18px'>✅ Country flags in the UI. ✅ Casing-style road/rail visuals (two-pass rendering). ✅ In-game player-buildable road/rail infrastructure ([[Buildable Infrastructure|→]]). Still open: deeper war/attacking-other-countries expansion.</span>\n\n<span style='font-size:16px'><i>🟡 3 of 4 done</i> — [[Map Rendering|→]] [[Buildable Infrastructure|→]]</span>\n\n</div>","x":1620,"y":0,"width":480,"height":320,"color":"#e8a600"},
		{"id":"s4b","type":"text","text":"<div style='text-align:center'>\n\n<span style='font-size:34px'><b>4.5 · Political &amp; Economic Realism</b></span>\n\n<span style='font-size:18px'>Six pillars in [[Vision Overview|→]] — a marathon, not a sprint. Pillar 1 core loop DONE: real government types + parties + real taxes + bills (vote or decree) + freedoms + regime change, all live and verified ([[Government, Legislature and Real Taxes|→]], [[Legislature and Bills|→]]). Still open: spending bills, AI legislating, elections reshuffling parliaments, and the other 5 pillars (sectors &amp; companies, conflicts/terrorism/military, unions, map/UI realism, data audits).</span>\n\n<span style='font-size:16px'><i>🟡 Pillar 1 core loop built — 5 pillars to go</i> — [[Vision Overview|→]]</span>\n\n</div>","x":2160,"y":0,"width":480,"height":320,"color":"#e8a600"},
		{"id":"s5","type":"text","text":"<div style='text-align:center'>\n\n<span style='font-size:34px'><b>5 · Finishing Stage</b></span>\n\n<span style='font-size:18px'>Close every remaining \"coming soon\" gap across all 8 ministries, balance-pass every sim number so no lever is a dead end, sand down UI edge cases (long names, small windows, extreme values), first-time onboarding pass.</span>\n\n<span style='font-size:16px'><i>⚪ Planned</i></span>\n\n</div>","x":2700,"y":0,"width":480,"height":320,"color":"#868e96"},
		{"id":"s6","type":"text","text":"<div style='text-align:center'>\n\n<span style='font-size:34px'><b>6 · Debugging Stage</b></span>\n\n<span style='font-size:18px'>Long soak-test play sessions across multiple terms, save/load stress-tested across patch versions, adversarial multi-angle code review passes, low-end performance profiling.</span>\n\n<span style='font-size:16px'><i>⚪ Planned</i></span>\n\n</div>","x":3240,"y":0,"width":480,"height":320,"color":"#868e96"},
		{"id":"s7","type":"text","text":"<div style='text-align:center'>\n\n<span style='font-size:34px'><b>7 · First Version (v1.0)</b></span>\n\n<span style='font-size:18px'>Tag a release build — the first complete, playable version of Meridian, distributed as a Windows executable.</span>\n\n<span style='font-size:16px'><i>🟣 Milestone</i></span>\n\n</div>","x":3780,"y":0,"width":480,"height":320,"color":"#9c36b5"},
		{"id":"legend","type":"text","text":"<div style='text-align:center'><span style='font-size:22px'>\n\nEach session's actual delta — what shipped, what's next — is recorded in <b>CLAUDE.md</b> at the repo root (updated after every programming session so a session on another device picks up with full context).\n\n</span></div>","x":0,"y":420,"width":1080,"height":140}
	],
